{
  "doc_id": "36213",
  "text": "Of the 57 million estimated deaths in 2008, cardiovascular diseases were responsible for 17 million deaths, of these, 80% occurred in low and middle-income countries [1] . Hypertension is recognized as a major risk factor of cardiovascular disease [CITATION_1] . In 2010 it was identified as the primary risk factor for global burden of disease, with 7% of global disability-adjusted life years (DALYs) [CITATION_2] . Nearly a quarter of the world´s adult population had hypertension in 2000 and an increase of 60% was forecast for 2025. At the same time, in sub-Saharan Africa (SSA) a faster increase was projected [CITATION_3] . This increasing trend was confirmed by another study, estimating 75 million people with hypertension in SSA in 2008 and 125 million in 2025 [5] .",
